<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-25T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/2524:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-25T18:00:00+03:00">April
                                        25, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 26—3:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1432. In reply to my inquiry as to any developments in the
                                Soviet-Rumanian situation Molotov informed me that Maniu’s proposal
                                made by Prince Stirbey to break away from Antonescu and to form a
                                new government in Soviet-occupied Rumania, although acceptable to
                                the Soviet Government, was not considered as having been made
                                seriously. He said that there were yet no different [<hi rend="italic">definite?</hi>] indications that Maniu would
                                follow such a course.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>